{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from hestonpy.models.heston import Heston\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt \n",
    "import time\n",
    "import numpy as np"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Initialisation of the model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "S0 = 100\n",
    "V0 = 0.06\n",
    "r = 0.05\n",
    "\n",
    "params = {\n",
    "    \"kappa\": 1,\n",
    "    \"theta\": 0.06,\n",
    "    \"sigma\": 0.3,\n",
    "    \"rho\": -0.5,\n",
    "    \"drift_emm\": 0.00,\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "heston = Heston(spot=S0, vol_initial=V0, r=r, **params)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "heston.price_surface()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "There are three different ways to price with an `Heston` object: Monte Carlo, Heston original formula and Carr-Madan"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Price via Monte Carlo"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Parameters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "nbr_points = 100\n",
    "nbr_simulations = 10**3"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Via Euler-Maruyama scheme"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Variance has been null 0 times over the 100000 iterations (0.0%) \n",
      "Monte Carlo Euler scheme in 0.0445s : price $12.06, std 0.49, and Confidence interval [12.02,12.11]\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "start_time = time.time()\n",
    "result = heston.monte_carlo_price(nbr_points=nbr_points, nbr_simulations=nbr_simulations, strike=100, time_to_maturity=1, scheme=\"euler\")\n",
    "time_delta = round(time.time() - start_time,4)\n",
    "price_euler = round(result.price, 2)\n",
    "std_euler = round(result.std, 2)\n",
    "infinum_euler = round(result.infinum, 2)\n",
    "supremum_euler = round(result.supremum, 2)\n",
    "print(f\"Monte Carlo Euler scheme in {time_delta}s : price ${price_euler}, std {std_euler}, and Confidence interval [{infinum_euler},{supremum_euler}]\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Via Milstein scheme"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Variance has been null 0 times over the 100000 iterations (0.0%) \n",
      "Monte Carlo Milstein scheme in 0.0577s : price $12.03, std 0.49, and Confidence interval [11.99,12.08]\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "start_time = time.time()\n",
    "result = heston.monte_carlo_price(nbr_points=nbr_points, nbr_simulations=nbr_simulations, strike=100, time_to_maturity=1, scheme=\"milstein\")\n",
    "time_delta = round(time.time() - start_time,4)\n",
    "price_milstein = round(result.price, 2)\n",
    "std_milstein = round(result.std, 2)\n",
    "infinum_milstein = round(result.infinum, 2)\n",
    "supremum_milstein = round(result.supremum, 2)\n",
    "print(f\"Monte Carlo Milstein scheme in {time_delta}s : price ${price_milstein}, std {std_milstein}, and Confidence interval [{infinum_milstein},{supremum_milstein}]\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Price via Fourier Transform"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Fourier Transform in 0.1561s : price $11.952, error $0.0 , and Confidence interval [11.952,11.952]\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "start_time = time.time()\n",
    "price_FT, error_FT = heston.fourier_transform_price(strike=100, time_to_maturity=1, error_boolean=True)\n",
    "time_delta = round(time.time() - start_time,4)\n",
    "infinum = round(price_FT-error_FT, 3)\n",
    "supremum = round(price_FT+error_FT, 3)\n",
    "price_FT = round(price_FT, 3)\n",
    "error_FT = round(error_FT, 8)\n",
    "print(f\"Fourier Transform in {time_delta}s : price ${price_FT}, error ${error_FT} , and Confidence interval [{infinum},{supremum}]\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Price via Carr-Madan formula "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Carr-Madan in 0.0896s : price $11.952, error $1.447e-10 , and Confidence interval [11.952,11.952]\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "start_time = time.time()\n",
    "price_CM, error_CM = heston.carr_madan_price(strike=100, time_to_maturity=1, error_boolean=True)\n",
    "time_delta = round(time.time() - start_time,4)\n",
    "infinum = round(price_CM-error_CM, 3)\n",
    "supremum = round(price_CM+error_CM, 3)\n",
    "price_CM = round(price_CM, 3)\n",
    "error_CM = round(error_CM, 14)\n",
    "print(f\"Carr-Madan in {time_delta}s : price ${price_CM}, error ${error_CM} , and Confidence interval [{infinum},{supremum}]\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Other"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Path simulations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1500x800 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "scheme = 'milstein'\n",
    "S, V = heston.plot_simulation(time_to_maturity=1, scheme=\"milstein\", nbr_points=252)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Characteristic function"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "One can do a sanity check of the characteristic functions used in the derivation of the Heston original formula "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "psi1 = heston.characteristic(j=1)\n",
    "psi2 = heston.characteristic(j=2)\n",
    "\n",
    "u = np.arange(start=-20, stop=20,step=0.01)\n",
    "\n",
    "x = np.log(S0)\n",
    "v = V0\n",
    "strike = 100\n",
    "time_to_maturity = 1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Check the real and imaginary parts"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x500 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(10,5), sharey=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot real part of psi1 and psi2\n",
    "axs[0].set_title(r'$\\mathfrak{Re}(\\psi_1)$ and $\\mathfrak{Re}(\\psi_2)$')\n",
    "axs[0].plot(u, np.abs(psi1(x, v, time_to_maturity, u)), label=r'$|\\psi_1|$', color='orange', linestyle='--')\n",
    "axs[0].plot(u, psi1(x, v, time_to_maturity, u).real, label=r'$\\psi_1$', color='orange')\n",
    "axs[0].plot(u, psi2(x, v, time_to_maturity, u).real, label=r'$\\psi_2$', color='blue')\n",
    "axs[0].grid(visible=True)\n",
    "axs[0].set_xlabel(r'$u$')\n",
    "axs[0].set_ylabel('Real part')\n",
    "axs[0].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot imaginary part of psi1 and psi2\n",
    "axs[1].set_title(r'$\\mathfrak{Im}(\\psi_1)$ and $\\mathfrak{Im}(\\psi_2)$')\n",
    "axs[1].plot(u, np.abs(psi1(x, v, time_to_maturity, u)), label=r'$|\\psi_1|$', color='orange', linestyle='--')\n",
    "axs[1].plot(u, psi1(x, v, time_to_maturity, u).imag, label=r'$\\psi_1$', color='orange')\n",
    "axs[1].plot(u, psi2(x, v, time_to_maturity, u).imag, label=r'$\\psi_2$', color='blue')\n",
    "axs[1].grid(visible=True)\n",
    "axs[1].set_xlabel(r'$u$')\n",
    "axs[1].set_ylabel('Imaginary part')\n",
    "axs[1].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show() "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "3D plot of the characteristic functions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 700x700 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(7,7))\n",
    "ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')\n",
    "ax.plot(u, psi1(x, v, time_to_maturity, u).real, psi1(x, v, time_to_maturity, u).imag, label=r'$\\psi_1$', color='orange')\n",
    "ax.plot(u, psi2(x, v, time_to_maturity, u).real, psi2(x, v, time_to_maturity, u).imag, label=r'$\\psi_2$', color='blue')\n",
    "ax.set_xticks([-5*i for i in range(6)] + [5*i for i in range(6)])\n",
    "ax.set_yticks([-1, 0, 1])\n",
    "ax.set_zticks([-1, 0, 1])\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('u')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Real part')\n",
    "ax.set_zlabel('Imaginary part')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Check the integrability over $R_+$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "/home/theo/Documents/packages/hestonpy/src/hestonpy/models/heston.py:258: RuntimeWarning: divide by zero encountered in divide\n",
      "  gj = lambda u: (rho * sigma * u * 1j - bj - dj(u)) / (\n",
      "/home/theo/Documents/packages/hestonpy/src/hestonpy/models/heston.py:258: RuntimeWarning: invalid value encountered in divide\n",
      "  gj = lambda u: (rho * sigma * u * 1j - bj - dj(u)) / (\n",
      "/home/theo/Documents/packages/hestonpy/src/hestonpy/models/heston.py:264: RuntimeWarning: invalid value encountered in divide\n",
      "  - 2 * np.log((1 - gj(u) * np.exp(dj(u) * tau)) / (1 - gj(u)))\n",
      "/home/theo/Documents/packages/hestonpy/src/hestonpy/models/heston.py:267: RuntimeWarning: invalid value encountered in divide\n",
      "  lambda tau, u: (bj - rho * sigma * u * 1j + dj(u))\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "psi1 = heston.characteristic(j=1)\n",
    "integrand1 = lambda u : np.real((np.exp(-u * np.log(strike) * 1j) * psi1(x, v, time_to_maturity, u))/(u*1j)) \n",
    "psi2 = heston.characteristic(j=2)\n",
    "integrand2 = lambda u : np.real((np.exp(-u * np.log(strike) * 1j) * psi2(x, v, time_to_maturity, u))/(u*1j)) \n",
    "\n",
    "u = np.arange(start=0, stop=40,step=0.01)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure()\n",
    "plt.plot(u, integrand1(u) * u**2, label=\"Integrand 1\")\n",
    "plt.plot(u, integrand2(u) * u**2, label=\"Integrand 2\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(r'u')\n",
    "plt.ylabel(r'Integrand $\\times u^2$')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.grid(visible=True)\n",
    "plt.title(r'Existence of $Q_1$ and $Q_2$')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
 ],
